                        <p>A bug tracking system or defect tracking system is a software application that keeps track of reported 
                        software bugs in software development projects. It may be regarded as a type of issue tracking system. 
                        A bug tracking system is usually a necessary component of a good software development infrastructure, and 
                        consistent use of a bug or issue tracking system is considered one of the "hallmarks of a good software team.</p>
                        <p>In this Bug Tracking Software I have focused on usability through attractive and friendly user interface. 
                        It allows four user roles. Admin user has full access to all available actions such as adding and deleting 
                        projects, tickets and modifying roles. Project Manager can create Projects and assign users to projects.
                        Developers can edit ticket attributes as well as reassign tickets to another developer. Submitter is the lowest 
                        priority. Submitter can only add ticket and comments.</p>
